>>8c4f8d25-6288-4dd7-92ab-5313ef5fd59f
Seems pretty user friendly to me. Not a lot of normies on clearnet 8chan anyway. I doubt most would have any problem with ZeroNet. Getting on ZeroNet is easier than configuring a VPN, for basic usage anyway.

>>516c8312-9c2d-4f0f-9755-7b62503dd0a1
8chan is going to be on a short leash by feds going forward. The more people here the better.

The only reason I'd go back is to sow division and point people here.

>>55327a6b-d362-43be-a276-efdba92e795c
I think the 08chan.net anon has the right idea but I'd prefer if the poster image contained more details and not just a redirect to 08chan.net. Also not fond of the premade 08chan distribution from the site.

Get people on fast and give them more info on security setup later.

>>fee6cbd0-fb58-4f65-95e4-088f239d7a6c
Also might check that your site can handle enough traffic. I just went there for review and it gave me a "too many requests" error.

posts.subject: 08chan propaganda
posts.body:
What propaganda are we going to use to get people over here?

The 08chan.net guy had a good idea but his site has been down for a while. So that is a problem.

I put this quick guide together. Open to suggestions to improve it.

>>13fd05c6-191a-45fb-91bb-1c686538d8ca
Optional? We have that onionshare guy and who knows who else in the future that might post illegal content. I'd hate to recommend anybody take a less secure route.

>>62911b5d-b8ab-4634-a585-24eb052b7183
Oh yeah, thanks. That was just my thinking about it. Not even sure my "poster" thing is the way to go. It all might happen organically anyway as people on the clearnet chans talk about it.

>>900598c2-0a70-494f-b80d-7d2ed8751ef4

Like the idea but IOTBW relied on causing a negative reaction in leftists and subsequent reaction in normies: "Wait. Do these people think it -isn't- ok to be white??" Really pretty clever.

Saw another one that comes close to the same level of trolling, "Islam is right about women." Maybe a "Judaism is right about white people" ??

>>9a586367-7402-4df1-bf32-d75a108cb2f0
Looks sad. Why so few dots? I have more but I'm running TOR only.

>>5311feb9-80b8-482c-b2b1-37d87e1bc224
Think this effort is doomed. Once the key generation becomes more distributed people will probably just be making fresh keys regularly.

>>6325f0ee-8d44-4ce6-8b53-9ebb3df2923f
16chan and blockchan allow torposting. Spacechan doesn't even have a /pol/ last time I checked.

Not everyone who posts on imageboards wants to foment rebellion. Some people just want to shitpost.

>>ad5e7f81-8fed-48d9-9f55-d5965e5eff3c
If Neinchan is trying to be the edgy "Nazi" board but isn't allowing torposting then that would be a...nein...from me.

I agree that torposting is an important feature going forward. Would need to hear some really good reasons if it wasn't allowed.

>>9f479ee5-1327-417e-a4ac-a7eb69c4087a
We'd really be screwed without the GPL and open source licenses in general. Some company developing a closed source package you like goes belly up? You're toast. With FOSS when devs get bored others can take over. Or if there are big disagreements they can fork.

You can build a server with virtualization (XCP-ng), firewall/IDS/etc (OPNSense), really most stuff you would want and it's all yours and legal; nobody is coming after you for license issues.

Don't like Amazon's AWS? Set up your own cloud with MaaS/OpenStack/Mist. FOSS gives users freedom regardless of the political bent of devs.

Stallman did good.
